{"type":"message","id":"d062f8d7","parentId":"87becd5c","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:07:49.931Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"write_1771164465686_220","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 3000 bytes to docs_archive/KNOWLEDGE_BASE.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771164469929}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ebf917c","parentId":"d062f8d7","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:07:49.936Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771164468198_221","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MASTER PROTOCOL\n\n## 1. Thinking Loop\n- **<thinking>** blocks must be used for complex reasoning before tool usage.\n- Sub-agents must output their reasoning clearly within `<thinking>` tags before executing multi-step plans.\n- This ensures traceability and allows for better debugging and context management.\n\n## 2. Menu Management\n- Always clear existing commands with `deleteMyCommands` before setting new ones to prevent ghost entries.\n\n## 3. Strategy: Inventory Lag Exploit\n- Aggressively call `/inventory/sync` on targets during Steam updates to catch mispriced cached items.\n\n## System Capabilities\n- **grep-master:** Lazy load implementation for large file searching.\n- **bat-cat:** Syntax highlighted reading for better code visibility.\n- **self-improving-agent:** Error loop analysis and self-correction mechanism.\n- **random-forest-predictor:** Price prediction using Random Forest ML model.\n- **websockets-stable:** Stable WebSocket connection manager with auto-reconnect.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771164469935}}
